<br>
The opening of Bloody Kithicor is another example of this... also the corruption of Lesser Faydark, and the plague in the Karanas were like this, although, Verant was inconsistent with the last two story lines... I don't think Karanas were ever under plague on our server, and I remember some servers had the green sky and some didn't.<br>
<br>
What's always odd to me is that the elves in the outpost on Kunark have never bothered to knock down all those iksar statues, or bothered to fortify that city in any way.  I always thought it would be neat if I one day roamed over to Firiona Vie City and saw new statues of Tunare and FV being erected in place of those massive lizards.  It wouldn't affect gameplay in any way.  It just seems silly that in however many hundreds of years pass in EQ time, that most things remain exactly the same.  Surely deserts will return to full bloom, jungles will thin out, lakes will dry up, and the like.  Aesthetic changes. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uarthur265.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Arthur265</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 95<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/23/02 3:39:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2762.topic&index=25>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> What are the alternatives?</span><hr size=1> Yes, there are definitely technical difficulties with this type of game, and, yes, there is more that could have been done with EQ.  I think most of us could also see what that guide made painfully obvious too.<br>
<br>
So, now the big question... What other game is better? <p><A HREF="http://eq.guildmagic.com/character.cfm?ID=169421">Trevian</A><br>
