</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ujaranna.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jaranna</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 33<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/23/02 3:56:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2762.topic&index=26>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What are the alternatives?</span><hr size=1> I keep brining this up, but I'll mention it again.<br>
<br>
Asheron's Call had monthly updates that not only added things to the world, but changed it.  One day I logged in to find my hometown had been destroyed by Shadows.  One day it was there, the next it was a crater with a shadow spire hovering over it.<br>
<br>
Very cool.  They destroyed another town as well with that update.<br>
<br>
According to AC lore, Bael'Zharon had been imprisoned by 4 sould crystals.  One month, three new dungeons were added, the final &quot;boss&quot; of each was a crystal.  These dungeons were for different level ranges, as well, so the low-levels could actually do something worthwhile.<br>
<br>
Then the next month, another dungeon was opened, with another crystal.  The inside of the dungeon was a PvP area.  Not only did you have to deal with shadows and crystal shards, but there were also PCs defending the last crystal to keep Bael'Zharon imprisoned.  Eventually, though, the fourth crystal was shattered and Bael'Zharon was unleashed upon Dereth.<br>
<br>
Turbine really allowed players to affect the world in a way Verant hasn't.  I would love to see some of this make it into EQ2 or later updates of EQ, but I'm not sure if the game engine would allow for it. <p><P>Jaranna<BR>
Circle of Sisters</P>
